# .ckignore — scope ck's semantic/lexical index to production TypeScript only.
#
# Mirrors @vt/measures' isProductionSourcePath — the repo's canonical
# "production source" definition, used by the call-graph and health metrics
# (packages/measures/src/_shared/graph/call-graph.ts). Keeping ck's index in
# lock-step means `ck --sem` searches the same code the graph reasons about:
# core .ts/.tsx, minus tests, fixtures, generated, config, build output, and
# shell/edge code under scripts/ and bin/.
#
# Syntax is gitignore-compatible. This is a whitelist: ignore everything, keep
# traversing directories, re-include TypeScript, then re-exclude the
# non-production TypeScript that slips through.

# 1. Ignore everything by default.
*
# 2. Keep descending into directories (so the re-includes below are reachable).
!*/
# 3. Re-include TypeScript sources.
!*.ts
!*.tsx

# 4. Re-exclude non-production TypeScript files (later patterns win).
*.d.ts
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.spec.ts
*.spec.tsx
*.config.ts

# 5. Re-exclude non-production directories anywhere in the tree.
#    A file under an excluded directory cannot be re-included, so these
#    override the *.ts re-inclusion above for everything they contain.
**/__tests__/
**/__generated__/
**/integration-tests/
**/tests/
**/scripts/
**/bin/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/node_modules/

# 6. Foreign trees mounted in the worktree but NOT part of the product source —
#    each is its own nested git repo (untracked by this repo, so isProductionSourcePath
#    never sees them): the standalone `brain` automation/agent repo, the
#    vendored Quartz static-site generator for the website, and the standalone
#    voicetree-evals benchmark repo.
/brain/
/vt-website-quartz/
/voicetree-evals/
